{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773433280244,"sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dc5366001BgXnbEPa5d4Xr2","sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","messageID":"msg_ce8dc3ea2001O2QEze2T8l4Xed","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_019qPQqoJXqZXxuXn4EXRf89","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n2: \n3: This file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\n4: If you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n9: \n10: These are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n11: \n12: ### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n13: \n14: ```\n15: # CORRECT — runs local source directly\n16: bun dev <command> [args...]\n17: \n18: # WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\n19: wombo <command> [args...]\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Why:** wombo is dogfooded — we develop it using itself. The global binary is a\n23: snapshot from the last release. If you use it, you're testing old code, not your\n24: changes. `bun dev` runs `bun src/index.ts` which executes the current working tree.\n25: \n26: **Examples:**\n27: ```sh\n28: bun dev help\n29: bun dev tasks list\n30: bun dev tasks add my-feat \"My Feature\" --priority high\n31: bun dev launch --dry-run --all-ready\n32: bun dev init --force\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Never publish to npm\n36: \n37: Distribution is GitHub-only. Users install via:\n38: ```sh\n39: bun install -g github:fulgidus/wombo\n40: ```\n41: Do not add `publishConfig`, do not run `npm publish`, do not add `.npmrc`.\n42: \n43: ### 3. Keep bun.lock committed\n44: \n45: The lockfile is committed for reproducible installs from GitHub. Always commit\n46: `bun.lock` after adding/removing/updating dependencies.\n47: \n48: ### 4. Do not commit user artifacts\n49: \n50: All wombo-combo user artifacts live under `.wombo-combo/` (config, tasks, archive,\n51: state, logs, history). This directory is gitignored.\n52: \n53: The template at `src/templates/tasks.yml` is the canonical source for the task\n54: file schema. The root `.wombo-combo/` dir is for local development only.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Project structure\n59: \n60: ```\n61: wombo/\n62:   package.json              # name: wombo-combo, version in sync with git tags\n63:   src/\n64:     index.ts                # CLI entry point, arg parsing, command routing\n65:     config.ts               # WomboConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n66:     commands/\n67:       init.ts               # Interactive guided setup (Prompter class)\n68:       launch.ts             # Launch a wave of agents\n69:       resume.ts             # Resume a stopped wave\n70:       status.ts             # Show wave status\n71:       verify.ts             # Build verification\n72:       merge.ts              # Merge verified branches\n73:       retry.ts              # Retry a failed agent\n74:       cleanup.ts            # Remove worktrees and sessions\n75:       tasks/\n76:         list.ts, add.ts, set-status.ts, check.ts, archive.ts, show.ts\n77:     lib/\n78:       tasks.ts              # Task file I/O, types, ensureTasksFile guard\n79:       state.ts              # Wave state persistence\n80:       prompt.ts             # Agent prompt generation\n81:       launcher.ts           # Process spawning\n82:       monitor.ts            # ProcessMonitor\n83:       worktree.ts           # Git worktree management\n84:       merger.ts             # Git merge operations\n85:       verifier.ts           # Build verification logic\n86:       ui.ts                 # Console dashboard\n87:       tui.ts                # neo-blessed TUI\n88:     templates/\n89:       tasks.yml             # Template with full schema docs\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## User-facing file layout\n93: \n94: All wombo-combo files live under `.wombo-combo/`:\n95: \n96: ```\n97: .wombo-combo/\n98:   config.json     # Project configuration (replaces wombo.json)\n99:   tasks.yml       # Active tasks (replaces .features.yml)\n100:   archive.yml     # Completed/cancelled tasks\n101:   state.json      # Wave state\n102:   logs/           # Agent log files\n103:   history/        # Wave history records\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Coding conventions\n107: \n108: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). Use Bun APIs where available (`Bun.file()`,\n109:   `Bun.spawn()`, etc.), fall back to Node stdlib when Bun doesn't have a\n110:   direct equivalent.\n111: - **Language:** TypeScript, strict mode. Run `bun run typecheck` to verify.\n112: - **Modules:** ESM only (`\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json). Use `.js`\n113:   extensions in import paths (TypeScript resolves them to `.ts` at runtime in Bun).\n114: - **No external CLI frameworks.** Arg parsing is hand-rolled in `index.ts`.\n115:   This is intentional — it keeps the dependency tree minimal and gives full\n116:   control for agent-readiness features (schema introspection, etc.).\n117: - **YAML library:** `yaml` (v2). Use `YAML.parse()` / `YAML.stringify()`.\n118: - **No npm registry dependencies** for core functionality. `neo-blessed` is\n119:   the only large dependency (TUI). Keep it that way.\n120: \n121: ## Testing and verification\n122: \n123: ```sh\n124: # Type check (no emit)\n125: bun run typecheck\n126: \n127: # Build (outputs to dist/)\n128: bun run build\n129: \n130: # Run any command via dev\n131: bun dev help\n132: bun dev tasks check\n133: ```\n134: \n135: There is no test suite yet. When adding tests, use Bun's built-in test runner\n136: (`bun test`).\n137: \n138: ## Known quirks\n139: \n140: - **Bun readline + piped stdin:** `rl.question()` silently fails after readline\n141:   emits `close`. The `Prompter` class in `src/commands/init.ts` works around\n142:   this using `rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]()` with `process.stdout.write()`.\n143: - **YAML null vs empty array:** `yaml` parses `tasks:` (no items) as `null`,\n144:   not `[]`. `loadTasks()` normalizes this: `parsed.tasks ?? parsed.features ?? null`.\n145: - **`import.meta.dir`:** Gives the directory of the current source file in Bun.\n146:   Used in `src/lib/tasks.ts` to resolve the template path.\n147: \n148: ## Feature backlog\n149: \n150: The active backlog lives in `.wombo-combo/tasks.yml` (local, gitignored). Use\n151: `bun dev tasks list` to see it. The canonical template is at\n152: `src/templates/tasks.yml`.\n153: \n154: ## Making changes\n155: \n156: 1. **Check the backlog:** `bun dev tasks list`\n157: 2. **Pick a feature/subtask:** `bun dev tasks show <id>`\n158: 3. **Mark it in-progress:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> in_progress`\n159: 4. **Implement the change**\n160: 5. **Typecheck:** `bun run typecheck`\n161: 6. **Build:** `bun run build`\n162: 7. **Test manually:** `bun dev <relevant-command>`\n163: 8. **Mark done:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> done`\n164: 9. **Commit** with a conventional commit message referencing the feature ID\n165: \n166: ## Version and release\n167: \n168: - Current version is in `package.json` → `\"version\"` field.\n169: - Git tags must match: tag `v0.0.1` ↔ `\"version\": \"0.0.1\"`.\n170: - Release workflow (when implemented) triggers on `v*` tag push to main.\n\n(End of file - total 170 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"# AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n\nThis file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\nIf you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n\n---\n\n## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\nThese are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n\n### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n\n```\n# CORRECT — runs local source directly\nbun dev <command> [args...]\n\n# WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\nwombo <command> [args...]\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773433280218,"end":1773433280239}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773433280631,"sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dc56e0001LOVVs1pY0W19Kb","sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","messageID":"msg_ce8dc3ea2001O2QEze2T8l4Xed","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01E2oA4bofb6F7U3EdFSeGMd","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/src/commands/tasks/check.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/src/commands/tasks/check.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * tasks/check.ts — Validate the tasks file for schema issues, broken deps, and orphans.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   woco tasks check\n6:  *\n7:  * Checks:\n8:  *   - Required fields present on every task\n9:  *   - No duplicate IDs\n10:  *   - All depends_on references point to existing tasks\n11:  *   - No circular dependencies\n12:  *   - No orphaned subtasks (subtask IDs unique)\n13:  *   - Priority/difficulty values are valid enums\n14:  *   - Effort strings are parseable ISO 8601 durations\n15:  */\n16: \n17: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\n18: import {\n19:   loadFeatures,\n20:   allFeatureIds,\n21:   parseDurationMinutes,\n22:   type Feature,\n23:   type Subtask,\n24:   type FeaturesFile,\n25: } from \"../../lib/tasks.js\";\n26: import {\n27:   VALID_STATUSES,\n28:   VALID_PRIORITIES,\n29:   VALID_DIFFICULTIES,\n30: } from \"../../lib/task-schema.js\";\n31: \n32: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n33: // Types\n34: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n35: \n36: export interface TasksCheckOptions {\n37:   projectRoot: string;\n38:   config: WomboConfig;\n39: }\n40: \n41: interface CheckResult {\n42:   errors: string[];\n43:   warnings: string[];\n44: }\n45: \n46: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n47: // Validation (enums imported from task-schema.ts — single source of truth)\n48: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n49: \n50: function collectAllItems(data: FeaturesFile): (Feature | Subtask)[] {\n51:   const items: (Feature | Subtask)[] = [];\n52:   const collect = (list: (Feature | Subtask)[]) => {\n53:     for (const item of list) {\n54:       items.push(item);\n55:       if (item.subtasks?.length) collect(item.subtasks);\n56:     }\n57:   };\n58:   collect(data.tasks ?? []);\n59:   collect(data.archive ?? []);\n60:   return items;\n61: }\n62: \n63: function checkTasks(data: FeaturesFile): CheckResult {\n64:   const errors: string[] = [];\n65:   const warnings: string[] = [];\n66:   const allItems = collectAllItems(data);\n67:   const allIds = allItems.map((i) => i.id);\n68:   const idSet = new Set<string>();\n69: \n70:   // Check for duplicates\n71:   for (const id of allIds) {\n72:     if (idSet.has(id)) {\n73:       errors.push(`Duplicate ID: \"${id}\"`);\n74:     }\n75:     idSet.add(id);\n76:   }\n77: \n78:   // Check each item\n79:   for (const item of allItems) {\n80:     const prefix = `[${item.id}]`;\n81: \n82:     // Required fields\n83:     if (!item.id) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: id`);\n84:     if (!item.title) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: title`);\n85:     if (!item.status) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: status`);\n86: \n87:     // Validate enum values\n88:     if (item.status && !(VALID_STATUSES as readonly string[]).includes(item.status)) {\n89:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid status: \"${item.status}\"`);\n90:     }\n91:     if (item.priority && !(VALID_PRIORITIES as readonly string[]).includes(item.priority)) {\n92:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid priority: \"${item.priority}\"`);\n93:     }\n94:     if (item.difficulty && !(VALID_DIFFICULTIES as readonly string[]).includes(item.difficulty)) {\n95:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid difficulty: \"${item.difficulty}\"`);\n96:     }\n97: \n98:     // Validate effort\n99:     if (item.effort) {\n100:       const minutes = parseDurationMinutes(item.effort);\n101:       if (minutes === Infinity) {\n102:         warnings.push(`${prefix} Unparseable effort duration: \"${item.effort}\"`);\n103:       }\n104:     }\n105: \n106:     // Check depends_on references\n107:     if (item.depends_on?.length) {\n108:       for (const dep of item.depends_on) {\n109:         if (!idSet.has(dep)) {\n110:           errors.push(`${prefix} Broken dependency: \"${dep}\" does not exist`);\n111:         }\n112:       }\n113:     }\n114:   }\n115: \n116:   // Check for circular dependencies (simple DFS)\n117:   const visited = new Set<string>();\n118:   const visiting = new Set<string>();\n119:   const depMap = new Map<string, string[]>();\n120:   for (const item of allItems) {\n121:     depMap.set(item.id, item.depends_on ?? []);\n122:   }\n123: \n124:   function hasCycle(id: string): boolean {\n125:     if (visiting.has(id)) return true;\n126:     if (visited.has(id)) return false;\n127:     visiting.add(id);\n128:     for (const dep of depMap.get(id) ?? []) {\n129:       if (hasCycle(dep)) {\n130:         errors.push(`Circular dependency detected involving: \"${id}\" → \"${dep}\"`);\n131:         return true;\n132:       }\n133:     }\n134:     visiting.delete(id);\n135:     visited.add(id);\n136:     return false;\n137:   }\n138: \n139:   for (const id of idSet) {\n140:     hasCycle(id);\n141:   }\n142: \n143:   // Warn about features with no effort estimate\n144:   for (const item of allItems) {\n145:     if (!item.effort || item.effort === \"PT0S\") {\n146:       warnings.push(`[${item.id}] No effort estimate`);\n147:     }\n148:   }\n149: \n150:   return { errors, warnings };\n151: }\n152: \n153: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n154: // Command\n155: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n156: \n157: export async function cmdTasksCheck(opts: TasksCheckOptions): Promise<void> {\n158:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n159: \n160:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n161:   const result = checkTasks(data);\n162: \n163:   const allItems = collectAllItems(data);\n164:   console.log(`\\nChecking ${config.tasksDir}/ (${allItems.length} items)...\\n`);\n165: \n166:   if (result.errors.length === 0 && result.warnings.length === 0) {\n167:     console.log(\"  All checks passed. No issues found.\");\n168:     return;\n169:   }\n170: \n171:   if (result.errors.length > 0) {\n172:     console.log(`  ERRORS (${result.errors.length}):`);\n173:     for (const e of result.errors) {\n174:       console.log(`    \\x1b[31m✗\\x1b[0m ${e}`);\n175:     }\n176:     console.log(\"\");\n177:   }\n178: \n179:   if (result.warnings.length > 0) {\n180:     console.log(`  WARNINGS (${result.warnings.length}):`);\n181:     for (const w of result.warnings) {\n182:       console.log(`    \\x1b[33m⚠\\x1b[0m ${w}`);\n183:     }\n184:     console.log(\"\");\n185:   }\n186: \n187:   if (result.errors.length > 0) {\n188:     process.exit(1);\n189:   }\n190: }\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/tasks/check.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * tasks/check.ts — Validate the tasks file for schema issues, broken deps, and orphans.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   woco tasks check\n *\n * Checks:\n *   - Required fields present on every task\n *   - No duplicate IDs\n *   - All depends_on references point to existing tasks\n *   - No circular dependencies\n *   - No orphaned subtasks (subtask IDs unique)\n *   - Priority/difficulty values are valid enums\n *   - Effort strings are parseable ISO 8601 durations\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadFeatures,\n  allFeatureIds,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773433280614,"end":1773433280629}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773433281352,"sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dc5869001rQYSgZViM7Ds6i","sessionID":"ses_31723c351ffe6G54611rxN573V","messageID":"msg_ce8dc3ea2001O2QEze2T8l4Xed","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01KgAXiDrwX1QgiNJ79Fj1bD","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/src/commands/tasks/archive.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-features-check/src/commands/tasks/archive.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * tasks/archive.ts — Move done/cancelled tasks to the archive section.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   woco tasks archive              # archive all done + cancelled\n6:  *   woco tasks archive <task-id>    # archive a specific task\n7:  *   woco tasks archive --dry-run    # show what would be archived\n8:  */\n9: \n10: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\n11: import {\n12:   loadFeatures,\n13:   saveFeatures,\n14:   findFeatureById,\n15:   type Feature,\n16: } from \"../../lib/tasks.js\";\n17: import { outputError, outputMessage, type OutputFormat } from \"../../lib/output.js\";\n18: \n19: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n20: // Types\n21: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n22: \n23: export interface TasksArchiveOptions {\n24:   projectRoot: string;\n25:   config: WomboConfig;\n26:   featureId?: string;\n27:   dryRun?: boolean;\n28:   outputFmt?: OutputFormat;\n29: }\n30: \n31: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n32: // Command\n33: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n34: \n35: export async function cmdTasksArchive(opts: TasksArchiveOptions): Promise<void> {\n36:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n37:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n38: \n39:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n40: \n41:   // Ensure archive array exists\n42:   if (!data.archive) {\n43:     data.archive = [];\n44:   }\n45: \n46:   let toArchive: Feature[];\n47: \n48:   if (opts.featureId) {\n49:     // Archive a specific feature\n50:     const idx = data.tasks.findIndex((f: Feature) => f.id === opts.featureId);\n51:     if (idx === -1) {\n52:       // Check if already in archive\n53:       if (data.archive.find((f) => f.id === opts.featureId)) {\n54:         outputMessage(fmt, `Task \"${opts.featureId}\" is already in the archive.`, {\n55:           already_archived: true,\n56:           id: opts.featureId,\n57:         });\n58:         return;\n59:       }\n60:       outputError(fmt, `Task \"${opts.featureId}\" not found.`);\n61:       return;\n62:     }\n63:     toArchive = [data.tasks[idx]];\n64:   } else {\n65:     // Archive all done + cancelled features\n66:     toArchive = data.tasks.filter(\n67:       (f: Feature) => f.status === \"done\" || f.status === \"cancelled\"\n68:     );\n69:   }\n70: \n71:   if (toArchive.length === 0) {\n72:     outputMessage(fmt, \"No tasks to archive.\", { count: 0 });\n73:     return;\n74:   }\n75: \n76:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n77:     outputMessage(fmt, `Would archive ${toArchive.length} task(s)`, {\n78:       dry_run: true,\n79:       count: toArchive.length,\n80:       features: toArchive.map((f) => ({ id: f.id, title: f.title, status: f.status })),\n81:     });\n82:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n83:       console.log(\"\");\n84:       for (const f of toArchive) {\n85:         console.log(`  ${f.id} — ${f.title} (${f.status})`);\n86:       }\n87:     }\n88:     return;\n89:   }\n90: \n91:   // Move features from active to archive\n92:   const archiveIds = new Set(toArchive.map((f) => f.id));\n93:   data.tasks = data.tasks.filter((f: Feature) => !archiveIds.has(f.id));\n94:   data.archive.push(...toArchive);\n95: \n96:   saveFeatures(projectRoot, config, data);\n97: \n98:   outputMessage(fmt, `Archived ${toArchive.length} task(s)`, {\n99:     count: toArchive.length,\n100:     features: toArchive.map((f) => ({ id: f.id, title: f.title, status: f.status })),\n101:   });\n102:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n103:     for (const f of toArchive) {\n104:       console.log(`  ${f.id} — ${f.title} (${f.status})`);\n105:     }\n106:   }\n107: }\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/tasks/archive.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * tasks/archive.ts — Move done/cancelled tasks to the archive section.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   woco tasks archive              # archive all done + cancelled\n *   woco tasks archive <task-id>    # archive a specific task\n *   woco tasks archive --dry-run    # show what would be archived\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadFeatures,\n  saveFeatures,\n  findFeatureById,\n  type Feature,\n} from \"../../lib/tasks.js\";\nimport { outputError, outputMessage, type OutputFormat } from \"../../lib/output.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Types","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773433281224,"end":1773433281342}}}}
